program:
# Your program goes here
.begin
# Randomly set the target number
set #target R

.inputnum
outsc #msg #endmsg

.readkey
halt
inp
- r 60
set #key r

# User pressed enter
= *#key 842
jmp #guessnum r

~ *#key 841
jmp #postdel r

# User pressed delete, but first make sure that the guess has digits
= 0 *#guess
jmp #readkey r
/ *#guess 10
set #guess r
out &del 1
jmp #readkey 1

.postdel

# Make sure the key is a digit
> *#key 9
jmp #readkey r

# Make sure the guess won't exceed 1000
>= *#guess 100
jmp #readkey r

# All good, proceed with keypress
inp
out r 1
* *#guess 10
+ r *#key
set #guess r
jmp #readkey 1

.guessnum
out &nl 1

# Check if number is too low
>= *#guess *#target
jmp #postlow r

# Handle too low of a guess
outsc #low #endlow
set #guess 0
jmp #inputnum 1
.postlow

# Check if number is too high
= *#guess *#target
jmp #posthigh r

# Handle too high of a guess
outsc #high #endhigh
set #guess 0
jmp #inputnum 1
.posthigh

# Handle a correct guess
outsc #correct #endcorrect
set #target R
set #guess 0
jmp #inputnum 1
mmap:
# Allocated memory for your program goes here
.target
_1

.guess
_1

#The last key pressed
.key
_1
constant:
# Constant values for your program go here
.msg
'Guess a number 0-999:
:endmsg

.low
'Too low!
&nl
:endlow

.high
'Too high!
&nl
:endhigh

.correct
'That's correct!
&nl
'Ready to play again?
&nl
:endcorrect
